INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (4,1,'2017-08-08 06:50:08','2017-08-08 06:50:08','<div class=\"item\">\r\n[text* your-name placeholder \"* Name\"]\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"item\">\r\n[email* your-email placeholder \"* Email\"]\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"item\">\r\n[textarea* your-message placeholder \"* Message\"]\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"item check-submit clearfix\">\r\n<div class=\"captcha-cont clearfix\">\r\n[mailpoetsignup mailpoetsignup-13 list:2 default:on label-inside-span \"Fan Mail\"]\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"btn-submit clearfix\">\r\n[submit class:btn-style \"Submit\"]\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\n1\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThank you for your message. It has been sent.\nThere was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\nOne or more fields have an error. Please check and try again.\nThere was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\nYou must accept the terms and conditions before sending your message.\nThe field is required.\nThe field is too long.\nThe field is too short.\nThe date format is incorrect.\nThe date is before the earliest one allowed.\nThe date is after the latest one allowed.\nThere was an unknown error uploading the file.\nYou are not allowed to upload files of this type.\nThe file is too big.\nThere was an error uploading the file.\nThe number format is invalid.\nThe number is smaller than the minimum allowed.\nThe number is larger than the maximum allowed.\nThe answer to the quiz is incorrect.\nYour entered code is incorrect.\nThe e-mail address entered is invalid.\nThe URL is invalid.\nThe telephone number is invalid.','Contact form','','publish','closed','closed','','contact-form-1','','','2017-11-08 09:23:47','2017-11-08 09:23:47','',0,'http:///?post_type=wpcf7_contact_form&#038;p=4',0,'wpcf7_contact_form','',0),(5,1,'2017-08-08 06:50:22','2017-08-08 06:50:22','[wysija_page]','Subscription confirmation','','publish','closed','closed','','subscriptions','','','2017-08-08 06:50:22','2017-08-08 06:50:22','',0,'http:///?wysijap=subscriptions',0,'wysijap','',0),(9,1,'2017-08-08 06:58:52','2017-08-08 06:58:52','','Home','','publish','closed','closed','','home','','','2017-08-08 06:58:52','2017-08-08 06:58:52','',0,'http:///?page_id=9',0,'page','',0),(10,1,'2017-08-08 06:58:52','2017-08-08 06:58:52','','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','9-revision-v1','','','2017-08-08 06:58:52','2017-08-08 06:58:52','',9,'http:///2017/08/08/9-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(11,1,'2017-08-08 06:59:17','2017-08-08 06:59:17','Daryl L. James, Jr.s story is a history like none weve heard before. We learn in his book, <em>A Gay Mans Odyssey Through the 20th Century and Beyond,</em> what it was like to be a gay man in the Depression in Middle America, when he was outed in his junior year of high school and faced the terror of being set-up and arrested by the vice-squad in LA or being preyed upon by violent homophobes in Chicago. He is a proud veteran of both WWII and the Korean War, where he served as a radio man doing top-secret work in places like the Amazon and the island of Guam. He built his career in publishing and advertising, and worked on Madison Avenue and Hollywood. He survived both McCartheyism and the AIDS epidemic, suffering great loss as a result of each. His stories and the stories of the men and women he has loved strike a huge chord in our society today. Like Forrest Gump, Daryl has been on the ground and present, recording the details of many of our most amazing historic times and events.','Book','','publish','closed','closed','','book','','','2018-07-10 05:50:53','2018-07-10 05:50:53','',0,'http:///?page_id=11',0,'page','',0),(12,1,'2017-08-08 06:59:17','2017-08-08 06:59:17','','About the Book','','inherit','closed','closed','','11-revision-v1','','','2017-08-08 06:59:17','2017-08-08 06:59:17','',11,'http:///2017/08/08/11-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(13,1,'2017-08-08 06:59:25','2017-08-08 06:59:25','It is Daryl L. James, Jr.s love for the written word that constantly encourages him to write. At 92, he has experienced the countrys great struggles and great triumphs. He survived the Great Depression, and he joined the US Navy during World War II and Korean War. After being discharged, he pursued a career in magazine publishing.','Author','','publish','closed','closed','','author','','','2018-07-10 05:50:30','2018-07-10 05:50:30','',0,'http:///?page_id=13',0,'page','',0),(14,1,'2017-08-08 06:59:25','2017-08-08 06:59:25','','About the Author','','inherit','closed','closed','','13-revision-v1','','','2017-08-08 06:59:25','2017-08-08 06:59:25','',13,'http:///2017/08/08/13-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(15,1,'2017-08-08 07:00:10','2017-08-08 07:00:10','It was during this visit that my eyes fell upon the most beautiful piece of mens clothing that screamed for my attention and purchase. It was elegant. It was billowy, and without a doubt, the most beguiling yellow shirt I had ever seen. I luxuriated in the elegant opulence of its seductive silkiness that scintillated every fiber of my upper body. I knew that this shirt was me. I would wear it proudly, perhaps subconsciously flaunting my true identity to the rampant homophobia of those times. One caveat temporarily quashed the sale. My dear daddy recognized the not-so-subtle implications of this purchase.\r\n\r\nI feel compelled to break a self-imposed silence on my recall of Rock Hudsons marriage to Phyllis Gates in the mid-fifties of the last century. Meeting Phyllis in 1953, at the notorious Tropical Village gay bar and beach in Venice, California, we immediately established a close bond. First of all, she was a gorgeous woman, very feminine, untypical of the lesbian image of that era. She was having problems with a girl friend working in Las Vegas, and I related, since I too was having similar problems with my sailor boyfriend serving on a cruiser in the Korean War.\r\n\r\nDecember 31, 1999, the last hours of the last day of the year, decade, century, and millennium; with these final moments ebbing away. I feel a need to experience every precious second. For me to leave behind the 20th Century is traumatic. An era is quickly moving into the history books, and I am not sure I am ready to say good-bye to a period of time that covers so much of my life. Arriving on the planet back in 1926, it has been my privilege to observe 74 percent of the century.\r\n','Excerpts','','publish','closed','closed','','excerpts','','','2018-07-10 05:50:04','2018-07-10 05:50:04','',0,'http:///?page_id=15',0,'page','',0),(16,1,'2017-08-08 07:00:10','2017-08-08 07:00:10','','Excerpts','','inherit','closed','closed','','15-revision-v1','','','2017-08-08 07:00:10','2017-08-08 07:00:10','',15,'http:///2017/08/08/15-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(17,1,'2017-08-08 07:00:22','2017-08-08 07:00:22','','Blog','','publish','closed','closed','','blog','','','2017-08-08 07:00:22','2017-08-08 07:00:22','',0,'http:///?page_id=17',0,'page','',0),(18,1,'2017-08-08 07:00:22','2017-08-08 07:00:22','','Blog','','inherit','closed','closed','','17-revision-v1','','','2017-08-08 07:00:22','2017-08-08 07:00:22','',17,'http:///2017/08/08/17-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(19,1,'2017-08-08 07:00:29','2017-08-08 07:00:29','Hello! Thanks for stopping by. Is there anything you would like to share with me before you go? I would be happy to know your story. \r\n','Contact','','publish','closed','closed','','contact','','','2018-07-10 05:51:18','2018-07-10 05:51:18','',0,'http:///?page_id=19',0,'page','',0),(20,1,'2017-08-08 07:00:29','2017-08-08 07:00:29','','Contact','','inherit','closed','closed','','19-revision-v1','','','2017-08-08 07:00:29','2017-08-08 07:00:29','',19,'http:///2017/08/08/19-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(27,1,'2017-08-08 07:25:31','2017-08-08 07:25:31','','<i class=\"fas fa-home\"></i>Home','','publish','closed','closed','','27','','','2018-07-10 07:47:12','2018-07-10 07:47:12','',0,'http:///?p=27',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(28,1,'2017-08-08 07:25: